{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Test contract frozen before code: authoritative contract is the ticket AC plus the existing scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py bare invocation. Preconditions: a stateful fake subprocess receives exactly [jscpd,--reporters,json,--output,<temp>,<scan-root>] and writes a production-shaped jscpd-report.json; absence injects FileNotFoundError at that subprocess seam. Production path: shared _jscpd.run_jscpd consumed by public jscpd_dup.analyze and the existing backfill clone reader. Tier: in-process unit/contract tests with a stateful verified CLI fake because the external jscpd binary is irreducible and absent from gating CI; a live known-clone canary is supplementary/skip-if-absent. Observable postconditions: exact clones/percentage, AnalyzerResult.duplication, exact Unavailable reason/accruing_since, and unchanged backfill clone count. Negative controls: nonzero/missing report must not become zero metrics. Collateral invariant: backfill uses the same bare command contract and retains its int clone_count shape. Recovery/statefulness: read-only temp report, no recovery contract."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784849773237500001,"uuid":"c3d4ecf0-ca42-4c99-9819-b84c8879aadb"}